- [medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:1003 (concurrency/races): On first mount when dashboard-suggestions config has not been fetched yet and resolves enabled, fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig mutates dashboardSuggestionsConfigFetched/dashboardSuggestionsEnabled, which triggers the watcher above to call loadDashboardSuggestionState(). The onMounted continuation then immediately calls loadDashboardSuggestionState() again before the first in-flight call has set loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor, so both dashboard-suggestions endpoints can be requested twice for the same SSP. This violates the intended once-per-SSP fetch behavior and adds avoidable duplicate API load/state churn.
